<h2>1. Daffodil Blankets</h2>

<p>I’m very lucky that daffodils seem to be the flower of choice in a lot of the grassy verges where I live. While a few individual ones come out in February, it’s around March that the whole area lights up. It’s like a yellow starry blanket. Rows and rows of them. It’s like a very loud sign saying “Spring is here!”</p>

<p>Daffodils are also called narcissus, with many different varieties. I find the bright yellow or orange ones my favourite but there are also white ones, often with orange trumpets, making them look a little like a fried egg. Very appropriate for an Easter flower.</p>

