<h2>5. Daisies</h2>
<p>Along with dandelions, daisies were integral to my childhood. Whether we were sitting in my grandmother’s garden with my sisters, in the playground with my school friends, or out in a park with my family, there were always daisies…and daisy chains. </p>

<p>We would spend time finding the best daisies, then very carefully splitting their stems, and threading them together. I would say we spent hours doing this, but the time passed so easily, it felt like there was no time at all. Soon we were all adorned with crowns and bracelets of flowers, making them for each other, and delicately putting them around each others wrists and heads.</p>

<p>Like the dandelions, they also close at night and open in the day. I love that they look like little spots of white, but up close have tinges of pink.</p>

<p>In a time of rushing, I feel daisies show the joy of living for the little things.</p>

