<h2>6. Baby rabbits</h2>

<p>I love when the babies come out. They’re so tiny! They look like they’d sit in the palm of your hand. Plus they have so much energy, they just bounce around. It’s so cute.</p>

<p>Although wild rabbits give birth multiple times a year, I find seeing baby rabbits in Spring particularly sweet. I’m very lucky that there are two burrows in the city so I get to regularly see rabbits hopping around. I’ve found the best time is around sunset, or in the mornings, so I’d recommend going on walks around green areas where you to live to see if there are any about.</p>

